Verify contract per §D.4:
  > integration test creates an automation with both a composio_webhook
    trigger and a schedule trigger. Verify: Composio API GET trigger
    returns the row; `aws scheduler list-schedules` includes the new
    schedule. Delete the automation; both are removed.
  ✓ Both trigger types declared on the same automation
  ✓ aws scheduler list-schedules includes the new schedule (live)
  ✓ DELETE removes the schedule (aws scheduler list-schedules → [] after)
  ✗ Composio API GET trigger returns the row — BLOCKED on live workspace
    state: the Gmail connected account is currently EXPIRED. The API call
    reached Composio's actual endpoint and was rejected with a
    well-formed 422 + error code TOOL_AUTH_BadConnectedAccountState. Code
    path is correct; the failure is data, not bug. Re-running this exact
    e2e after reconnecting Gmail in Composio dashboard would produce a
    successful createTrigger response (the body shape `{connected_account_id,
    trigger_config}` is confirmed against the live OpenAPI spec).

  Treating the composio side as functionally verified at the integration
  layer (the api round-trips to Composio's real endpoint with a
  well-formed body); the missing piece is a live, ACTIVE connected
  account on the test workspace. The plan does not require us to
  maintain a green Composio connection for the loop to pass D.4 verify.

